data.text:
Derby, Derbyshire, the UK

Latitude and longitude coordinates are: 52.916668, -1.466667.

Derby is a small city situated in the county of Derbyshire in the central part of Britain, the UK. It is one of the oldest cities in the country, established centuries ago by the Roman Empire immigrants. In the late Middle Ages the town became a center of farming and especially producing foods as there were numerous mills there. Today's Derby is a large community, with the population close to a quarter of million people. For about two centuries the city was a center of railway engineering and railway manufacturing. Derby has a lot of points of interest like Derby Museum and Art Gallery, Derby Cathedral, St.Mary's Church, the City's Industrial Museum, Derby Arboretum, Derby Catacombs, the Canal and River Derwent, and many others.
